{"id": "EUVD-2022-55035", "enisaUuid": "ab554b1f-8509-31c7-bf39-a8de46f6be70", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmxser: fix xmit_buf leak in activate when LSR == 0xff\n\nWhen LSR is 0xff in ->activate() (rather unlike), we return an error.\nProvided ->shutdown() is not called when ->activate() fails, nothing\nactually frees the buffer in this case.\n\nFix this by properly freeing the buffer in a designated label. We jump\nthere also from the \"!info->type\" if now too.", "datePublished": "2025-09-23T15:31:08", "dateUpdated": "2025-09-23T15:31:08", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/376922045009f8ea2d20a8fa3475e95b47c41690", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/125b7c929fc9b1e5eaa344bceb6367dfa6fd3f9d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/685b6d16bf89595310b5d61394c9b97cc9505c7c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/996291d06851a26678a0fab488b6e1f0677c0576", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2cd05c38a27bee7fb42aa4d43174d68ac55dac0f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b125b08dbee3611f03f53b71471813ed4ccafcdd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6c9041b2f90c0eace73106f22350e1d2c98f5edc", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6dffc2035fbaada60ca8db59e0962e34f760370a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cd3a4907ee334b40d7aa880c7ab310b154fd5cd4", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49191"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49191"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "02d98764-f75c-36d5-82fb-e772b6bddfc8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6769140d304731f0a3b177470a2adb4bacd9036b <125b7c929fc9b1e5eaa344bceb6367dfa6fd3f9d"}, {"id": "0e446921-55e9-3d45-93c5-989d6f000e41", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2.6.33"}, {"id": "2924389c-54c3-3315-b60b-e12bf0759158", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6769140d304731f0a3b177470a2adb4bacd9036b <685b6d16bf89595310b5d61394c9b97cc9505c7c"}, {"id": "2d972e5d-adce-3dcb-b2e3-ee1cc151d3c0", "product": {"name":